@startuml AD_D01_View_Assigned_Patient_List

title AD_D01 — View Assigned Patient List

|Doctor|
|System|

|Doctor|

note
  Prerequisites:
  - Doctor is authenticated and has active session
  - At least one patient assigned by Administrator
end note

start

:Navigate to "My Patients"\nfrom main dashboard;

|System|

:Retrieve all patients assigned\nto the logged-in doctor;

if (Patients found?) then (no)
  :Show informational banner;\nProvide link to contact Administrator;
  |Doctor|
  stop
else (yes)
  :Display patient list:\n- Full name\n- Patient ID\n- Date of birth\n- Active IVF cycle phase\n- Next appointment date/time;
endif

|Doctor|

if (Apply filters?) then (yes)
  :Select filter criteria:\n(cycle phase / date / name);

  |System|

  :Refresh list to match\nfilter criteria;

  if (Results found?) then (no)
    :Display "No patients match\nyour criteria" message;\nShow reset button;
    |Doctor|
    :Reset filters or\nrefine criteria;
    |System|
    :Show full unfiltered list;
  else (yes)
  endif
else (no)
endif

|Doctor|

:Select patient row;

|System|

:Load patient's complete\nmedical record view;

|Doctor|

:View patient profile\nand take clinical action;

stop

@enduml
